  "headline": "QuickSort & MergeSort",
  "description": "QuickSort: average O(n log n), worst O(n²), in-place, not stable. Picks pivot, partitions, recurses. MergeSort: always O(n log n), stable, O(n) auxiliary space. Most practical sorts are hybrid (Timsort=merge+insertion).",
